==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nux vomica
<hw>Nux` vom"i*ca</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[NL., fr. L. <ets>nux</ets> a
nut + <ets>vomere</ets> to vomit.]</ety> <def>The seed of <spn>Strychnos
Nuxvomica</spn>, a tree which abounds on the Malabar and Coromandel
coasts of the East Indies. From this seed the deadly poisons known as
<xex>strychnine</xex> and <xex>brucine</xex> are obtained. The seeds are
sometimes called <xex>Quaker buttons</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nuytsia</ent>⟦br⟧
